# META.a2ml — Echidnabot meta-level information
[metadata]
version = "0.1.0"
last-updated = "2026-04-24"

[project-info]
license = "PMPL-1.0-or-later"
author = "Jonathan D.A. Jewell (hyperpolymath)"

[architecture-decisions]
# ADRs listed chronologically. Use `status = "superseded"` when replacing.

[[architecture-decisions.decision]]
id           = "ADR-001"
date         = "2026-04-24"
status       = "accepted-temporary"
title        = "Native MCP server (echidnabot-mcp) as documented BoJ-only-MCP exception"
context      = """
Estate policy (memory: feedback_boj_only_mcp) requires all MCP tools to route
through the BoJ server. Two reinforcing reasons this bot currently cannot:

  (a) Operational: the BoJ V-lang adapter was removed during the V-lang ban
      (2026-04-10) and the Zig replacement at boj-server/adapter/zig/src/ is
      empty. The BoJ server is therefore unreachable on this workstation.

  (b) Protocol: BoJ's cartridge transport is async message-bus; echidnabot is
      invoked synchronously by proof-operation agents (Sonnet executors,
      Haiku scouts) that need call-and-response semantics, matching the
      Bullshit Field double-loop design. BoJ does not yet provide that
      transport.

Package 7 needs MCP exposure so echidnabot is directly callable by AI
assistants — waiting for both (a) and (b) to resolve would indefinitely block
the double-loop actuation work.
"""
decision     = """
Ship a standalone binary `echidnabot-mcp` (src/bin/mcp_server.rs) implementing
MCP JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio with four tools: suggest_tactics,
record_tactic_outcome, list_outcome_history, corpus_refresh. The BoJ-only
rule remains canonical; this is a single-binary documented exception, not a
policy revision.

Exception block declared in AGENTIC.a2ml [exceptions.boj-only-mcp] with rule,
status, decision-date, reason, scope, sunset-condition, sunset-action,
upstream-tracking. Sunset is tied to BoJ supporting the double-loop feedback
protocol (reason b); the operational reason (a) resolves along the way.
"""
consequences = """
Positive: Package 7 double-loop actuation unblocked; echidnabot directly
testable by Claude Desktop / Claude Code. Tool logic (Reranker, CorpusDelta)
stays in the library crate, so it is reusable when the cartridge is restored.

Negative: Second MCP surface to maintain until retirement; drift risk if the
BoJ revival lags. Mitigated by: (a) retirement plan in
docs/MCP-TEMPORARY-EXCEPTION.adoc; (b) project memory
feedback_boj_mcp_exception_echidnabot; (c) no new standalone MCP servers
green-lit by this exception.
"""
retirement   = """
Triggered by: BoJ cartridge supports the double-loop feedback protocol
(tracked in boj-server STATE.a2ml, quarterly review).

Steps: port the four tool handlers into the existing
boj-server/cartridges/echidna-llm-mcp/ cartridge, verify parity against the
current direct-callable surface, remove the [[bin]] entry from Cargo.toml,
delete src/bin/mcp_server.rs, delete docs/MCP-TEMPORARY-EXCEPTION.adoc,
delete the [exceptions.boj-only-mcp] block in AGENTIC.a2ml, update the
memory file feedback_boj_mcp_exception_echidnabot to mark closed.
"""
cross-refs   = [
  "AGENTIC.a2ml [exceptions.boj-only-mcp]",
  "docs/MCP-TEMPORARY-EXCEPTION.adoc",
  "memory: feedback_boj_mcp_exception_echidnabot.md",
  "memory: feedback_boj_only_mcp.md (canonical policy — unchanged)",
]

[development-practices]
versioning = "SemVer"
documentation = "AsciiDoc"
build-tool = "just"

[maintenance-axes]
scoping-first = true
axis-1 = "must > intend > like"
axis-2 = "corrective > adaptive > perfective"
axis-3 = "systems > compliance > effects"
